---
Source:
  - Title: The Poetry of Enlightenment
    ISBN: 9781590303993
    Translator: Sheng Yen
By: Hung Chih
Page: 90
---
In this silent sitting,
whatever realms may appear,
the mind is very clear as to all the details,
yet everything is where it originally is,
in its own place.

The mind stays on one thought
for ten thousand years,
yet does not dwell on any forms,
inside or outside.
